Docker set up & troubleshooting 

- Docker --version = version of docker your running 
- Docker info = info about docker that helps with debugging later 
- Docker ps = all running containers 
- Docker ps -a = previously run containers 


 docker run hello-world = couldn’t find docker image locally so it pulls it from the  library (docker hub)
- It gets the newer version of hello-world docker image and prints message

1. Docker checks if hello-world image is present on your local machine 
2. If not then it pulls the image from the docker hub 
3. Docker creates container from the image and runs it 


Docker file 

- Series of instructions on how to build a docker image ( template )  each instruction is a layer 
- Allow for repeatable builds - same environment every time = consistancy 

Structure : 

FROM                     = specifies the base layer of the docker image - python/node etc 
^ 
WORKDIR               = sets the working directory for subsequently builds after + where every instructions will be executed *V*
^                            
RUN                        = executes commands in container 
^
COPY                      = copies files from host machine into container 

^
CMD                       = specifies which command to run when container starts 


